parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to a increased risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt gets stuck in its harness
the seat belt does not retract after buckling
the seat belt does not pull out or put back
the seat belt becomes tangled
the seat belt folds in by itself
the seat belt jams in the guide
the seat belt stays loose after buckling
the seat belt does not tighten after latching.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants of the vehicle are not provided with the necessary protection.
symptoms: Airbag warning light on the dashboard
airbags fail to deploy in a crash
severe crash damage to the vehicle without airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause unexpected distractions while driving, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without a crash or impact
minor injuries sustained due to unexpected airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frequent failure of headlight bulbs can significantly reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially during evening or night driving.
symptoms: Headlight bulbs burn out frequently
requiring replacement every few weeks or months
dim or reduced light output
difficulty seeing while driving at night.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Misaligned headlights can reduce visibility, making it difficult to see the road ahead, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Headlights are not adjusted properly
difficulty seeing while driving at night
headlight beams are not aligned correctly.
